        "text": "<https:\/\/jaspervdj.be\/turnstyle\/|Turnstyle> is a graphical <https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Esoteric_programming_language|esoteric programming language> loosely inspired by <https:\/\/www.dangermouse.net\/esoteric\/piet.html|Piet>. Both encode programs as images, however, the similarities end at the syntax level.\nWhere Piet is really a stack machine in disguise, Turnstyle is an encoding of the (untyped) <https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Lambda_calculus|Lambda calculus>. This allows for building more reusable images at a higher level of abstraction, while still keeping the specification small, making it relatively easy to develop new interpreters.",
